# migrated from tests/cases/pragma_stress.chat (hermetic + isolated, perf-held)
[mock hermetic]
!set PARROT0_BASE=
!set PARROT0_SESSION=
!set PARROT0_WORLD_FACTS=0
!set PARROT0_LANG=en
!reset

[test pragma_stress]
# gen142 (E3) STRESS: ~14 HELD-OUT phrasings the classifier was NOT coded
# against (none appear in pragma.chat or in mod_pragma's cue strings), across all
# the speech acts. Passing this proves the routing comes from turn-SHAPE FEATURES
# (opener class, content predicate, negation, stance predicate, hedge, open
# quantifier, topic frame), not a memorized phrase table — the anti-impostor
# crux of E3. Includes mixed social+content turns where the CONTENT task survives.

# --- soft request: a fresh imperative shape with an open-quantifier object.
> say anything that comes to mind
< Happy to. Pick a thread — your day, a small fact to remember, or something to reason about — and I'll run with it.
> share something with me please
< Happy to. Pick a thread — your day, a small fact to remember, or something to reason about — and I'll run with it.

# --- hesitation: held-out hedge wordings (suppose / probably).
> honestly i suppose it could be
< No pressure — we can take it slowly. What's on your mind?
> i probably misunderstood you
< No pressure — we can take it slowly. What's on your mind?

# --- disagreement: held-out negated stance predicates (correct / convinced).
> that is not quite correct though
< Fair enough — tell me where I went wrong, and we can take it from there.
> i am not convinced
< Fair enough — tell me where I went wrong, and we can take it from there.

# --- topic change: held-out modal/switch openers and fresh objects.
> can we move on to jazz
< Sure, let's talk about jazz. What about jazz is on your mind?
> shall we discuss painting
< Sure, let's talk about painting. What about painting is on your mind?
> let us switch to gardening
< Sure, let's talk about gardening. What about gardening is on your mind?

# --- MIXED social + content (the content task must survive the wrapper):
#     opener + a teaching/query pair, opener + arithmetic, opener + personal
#     memory with proper-name casing preserved. Each opener is peeled and the
#     residue re-dispatched, so the real task runs.
> plato is a philosopher
< Learned: philosopher(plato).
> okay is plato a philosopher
< Yes.
> so what is 5 plus 6
< 11.
> well, remember my dog is Bruno
< Got it: your dog is Bruno.
> what is my dog called
< Bruno.

